                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14119782" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 11:49:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t reproduce this in lucene, and it looks like the lucene index will never touch the &apos;reindex&apos; property. Could this be cause by some sort of failure in the indexing process that prevents the reindex to finish properly?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A (failing) unit test might be good to demo the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14119788" author="tmueller" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 11:59:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hm, strange, I can not reproduce the problem right now. I set the &quot;lucene&quot; index to &quot;reindex&quot;, then after some time it automatically switches to &quot;false.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14119789" author="tmueller" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 12:01:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe it was related to using a wrong configuration property (I used &quot;persistance&quot; instead of &quot;persistence&quot;), but I&apos;m not sure (I also don&apos;t see how why this should a an effect on the &quot;reindex&quot; property).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s keep it closed until we have a reproducible test case (if we find one).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14147414" author="amitjain" created="Thu, 25 Sep 2014 05:37:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for 1.0.6&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
